 @{b}Description:@{ub}

@{fg shine}A) Device name.@{fg text}
 It's the device name used for all operations. You must use the  same  rules
that are explained  into  the  @{"Shell use section" link "Shell" 0}. If  you  press  the button
localized  at  the  right  of  this  string  gadget,  you  can  activate the
@{"device selector" link "GuiX_DevWin" 0}.
 Using the special cyclic gadget, you can select one of this access mode:

 Std    <- Access with trackdisk.device compatibile commands
 SCSI   <- Access with SCSI direct commands
 IEC    <- Accesso trough IEC cable with C= 1541 compatibile commands

@{fg shine}B) File-disk name.@{fg text}
 It's the file name that are used for reading and writing operations.

@{fg shine}C) Starting cylinder slider.@{fg text}

@{fg shine}D) Ending cylinder slider.@{fg text}
 This sliders are equivalent to START and END options of  @{"Cli" link "Shell" 0}  and  indicate
the starting and ending cylinders to execute all operations.

@{fg shine}E) Start button.@{fg text}
 When this button is pressed, xFX is activated with ARexx messages.

@{fg shine}F) Function register.@{fg text}
 With this register, you can select the command that xFX executes  when  the
Start button is pressed:


                            @{" 12.3.1 Read     " link "GuiX_ReadWin" 0}

                            @{" 12.3.2 Write    " link "GuiX_WriteWin" 0}

                            @{" 12.3.3 Copy     " link "GuiX_CopyWin" 0}

                            @{" 12.3.4 Check    " link "GuiX_CheckWin" 0}
@endnode

@node "GuiX_ReadWin" "5.3.1 GuiX: Read"




     @{fg fill}+-+---------------------------------------------------------+-+-+
     |@{fg text}*@{fg fill}|@{fg text} GuiX - © 1997-98 Alessandro Pedretti                    @{fg fill}|@{fg text}%@{fg fill}|@{fg text}|@{fg fill}|
