      |                                                             |@{fg text}/@{fg fill}|
      +-------------------------------------------------------------+-+@{fg text}


 @{b}Description:@{ub}

@{fg shine}A) Destination device@{fg text}
 If the radio button  @{i}Device@{ui}  is  checked,  you  can  specify  the  name  of
destination device. You must use the same rules that are explained into  the
section @{"Shell use" link "Shell" 0}. You can use the  @{"device requester" link "GuiX_DevWin" 0}  pressing  the  special
button.

@{fg shine}B) Checkbox for special functions:@{fg text}
 Verify    ->  verifies each written cylinder.
 No Eject  ->  inhibits the automatic disk ejection at the end of copy.

@{fg shine}C) Disk buffer path.@{fg text}
 If you activate the copy with only one device  and  with  "on disk"  buffer
(radiobutton @{i}Disk Buffer@{ui}), you must specify the path, where a temporary file
can be created.

@{fg shine}D) Radiobuttons to select the copy method.@{fg text}
 Memory       ->  Copies with only one device: memory buffer.
 Disk Buffer  ->  Copies with only one device: "on disk" buffer.
 Device       ->  Copies with two compatible devices.
@endnode

