 If you activate this option, the automatic disk ejection (performed at  the
end of verify operation) is disabled.
@endnode

@node "GuiX_DevWin" "5.4 GuiX: Device requester"


 With the GuiX device requester, you can select with no limitations  mounted
or unmounted AmigaDOS devices and device  drivers.   It  has  the  following
structure:


      @{fg fill}+-+------------------------------------------------------+-+-+
      |@{fg text}*@{fg fill}|@{fg text} Device Selector                                      @{fg fill}|@{fg text}%@{fg fill}|@{fg text}|@{fg fill}|
      +-+------------------------------------------------------+-+-+
      |@{fg shine} /-------\\ /---------\\ /-------\\  +------- Geometry -------+@{fg fill}|@{fg text}
 A -> @{fg fill}|@{fg shine} |@{fg text}Mounted@{fg shine}| |@{fg text}Unmounted@{fg shine}| |@{fg text}Drivers@{fg shine}|  |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}/        +-+---------+-+-------++ | @{fg text}Device Driver @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| +-------------------------+-+ | |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} CC0:                    @{fg shine}|@{fg text}*@{fg shine}| | |@{fg text}          Unit @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} CD0:                    @{fg shine}| | | |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} DF0:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text} Size (KBytes) @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} DF1:                    @{fg shine}| | | |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} DF2:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}  Tot. Sectors @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} DH0:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}                        @{fg shine}|@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} DH1:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}   Sector Size @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|@{fg text} <- B
      @{fg fill}|@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} DH2:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}                        @{fg shine}|@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} PC0:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}     Cylinders @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} PC1:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}                        @{fg shine}|@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |@{fg text} PC2:                    @{fg shine}| | | |@{fg text}  Sectors/Cyl. @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |                         +-+ | |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |                         |@{fg text}=@{fg shine}| | |@{fg text}      Surfaces @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |                         +-+ | |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| |                         |@{fg text}=@{fg shine}| | |@{fg text} Sectors/Track @{fg shine}-        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}| +-------------------------+-+ | |                        |@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg shine}+-------------------------------+ +------------------------+@{fg fill}|
      |@{fg text}         +----------------------+ +--------+      +--------+@{fg fill}|@{fg text}
 C -> @{fg fill}|@{fg text}Device   |                      | |   @{u}O@{uu}k   | <- D | @{u}C@{uu}ancel |@{fg fill}|@{fg text} <- E
      @{fg fill}|@{fg text}         +----------------------+ +--------+      +--------+@{fg fill}|
      +----------------------------------------------------------+-+
      |                                                          |@{fg text}/@{fg fill}|
      +----------------------------------------------------------+-+@{fg text}


 @{b}Description:@{ub}

@{fg shine}A) Register of functions.@{fg text}

 @{" Mounted   " link "GuiX_DevMount" 0}  ->  Mounted AmigaDOS devices.

 @{" Unmounted " link "GuiX_DevUnMount" 0}  ->  Unmounted AmigaDOS device.

 @{" Device    " link "GuiX_DevDev" 0}  ->  Device drivers.

@{fg shine}B) Geometry of selected device.@{fg text}
 The geometry is showed automatically in Mounted e Unmounted mode, when  you
select  a  device  from  listview.  In  Device mode, you must press the Info
button to display the geometry.

@{fg shine}C) Name of selected device.@{fg text}
 You must use the same conventions explained into @{"Shell use" link "Shell" 0} section.

@{fg shine}D) Confirm button.@{fg text}
 Confirms the selected device.

@{fg shine}E) Cancel button.@{fg text}
 Cancels the selection and closes the window.



 @{b}@{u}Menu items:@{ub}@{uu}

 @{b}Device List@{ub}
  Rescan    <---  Reapeats the scansion of devices (short key @{fg shine}RAMIGA + R@{fg text})
  Close     <---  Closes the window (short key @{fg shine}RAMIGA + C@{fg text})

 @{b}Mode@{ub}
  Mounted   <---  Shows the mounted devices (short key @{fg shine}RAMIGA + M@{fg text})
  UnMounted <---  Shows the unmounted devices (short key @{fg shine}RAMIGA + U@{fg text})
  Drivers   <---  Shows the device drivers (short key @{fg shine}RAMIGA + D@{fg text})


 If you activate the IEC  access,  it's  not  possible  to  use  the  device
requester,  because  it's  substituted  by a slider that is showed into GuiX
main window. This slider allows to select the IEC unit  number  (from  8  to
11), like into following figure:



