 @{b}Description:@{ub}

@{fg shine}A) Devices listview.@{fg text}
 List of accessible device drivers. If you click on a device, the geometry is
@{b}NOT@{ub} showed.

@{fg shine}B) Unit slider.@{fg text}
 With this slider, you can select the unit number.

@{fg shine}C) Info button.@{fg text}
 Many   device   drivers   don't   support   the  trackdisk.device   command
TD_GETGEOMETRY,  so  crashing  your  system  because  this  command  is  not
recognized. If you press this button, you can  force  the  geometry  reading
with some risk. Thus in device  mode,  the  automatic  geometry  reading  is
disabled.  (see  the @{"section 6.1" link "Note" 0}).

@{b}Note:@{ub}
 If you activates the @{"IEC  mode" link "GuiX_Main" 0},  it's  not  possible  to  open  the  device
requester.  Into GuiX main window, the "Device" string gadget and the button
to open this requester are sobstiuted by a slider that allow to  select  the
IEC device unit (from 8 to 11).
@endnode

